<div>

  <h2>Legality</h2>

  <p><b>What is considered a clone?</b><br>
  A Pokémon is considered a clone if another Pokémon exists in the Porybox database that shares all the following characteristics:<br>
  <ul>
  <li>OT</li>
  <li>TID (Trainer ID)</li>
  <li>SID (Secret ID)</li>
  <li>PID (Pokémon ID)</li>
  <li>EC (Encryption Constant)</li>
  <li>Evolutionary line</li>
  </ul>
  For static PID events, the IVs of the Pokémon must also match in addition to the criteria listed above.
  </p>
  
  <p><b>Can I edit Pokémon with Porybox?</b><br>
  Porybox is a Pokémon viewer, not an editor. You will not be able to edit your Pokémon with it.
  </p>

